obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (17080)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Jallianwala Bagh National Memorial Act, 1951.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17080&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (17081)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17081&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Memorial" means the Jallianwala Bagh National Memorial to perpetuate the memory of those`
  line `killed or wounded on the 13th day of April, 1919, on the site known as the Jallianwala Bagh, Amritsar;`
  line
  line `(b) "Trust" means the Trust for the erection and management of the Memorial.`
  line
  line `(c) "Trustees" means the Trustees of the Jallianwala Bagh National Memorial.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (17082)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Objects of the Trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17082&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the Trust shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to erect and maintain suitable buildings, structures and parks at or near the site of the`
  line `Jallianwala Bagh in the city of Amritsar, to perpetuate the memory of those who were killed or`
  line `wounded on the 13th day of April, 1919, on the said site;`
  line
  line `(b) to acquire lands, buildings and other properties for the purposes of the Trust; and`
  line
  line `(c) to raise and receive funds for the purposes of the Memorial.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (17083)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Trustees of the Jallianwala Bagh National Memorial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17083&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Trustees of the Jallianwala`
  line `Bagh National Memorial shall be the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Prime Minister ---Chairperson,`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) the Minister in-charge of Culture,`
  line
  line `^3[(d) the Leader of Opposition recognised as such in the House of the People or where there is no`
  line `such Leader of Opposition, then the Leader of the single largest Opposition Party in`
  line `that House;]`
  line
  line `(e) the Governor of the State of Punjab,`
  line
  line `(f) the Chief Minister of the State of Punjab, and`
  line
  line `(g) three eminent persons to be nominated by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Trustees shall be a body corporate with perpetual succession by the name of the "Trustees of the`
  line `Jallianwala Bagh National Memorial" and a common seal, and in that name shall sue and be sued, and shall`
  line `have power acquire and hold property, to enter into contracts and to do all acts necessary for, and consistent`
  line `with, the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2006, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 21-12-2006).`
  line `2. Clause (b) omitted by Act 39 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-12-2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 5-12-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (17084)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Term of office of nominated Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17084&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Term of office of nominated Trustees.--The Trustees nominated under clause (g) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4 shall be Trustees for a period of five years, and shall be eligible for`
  line renomination.]
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the term of office of a Trustee nominated under clause (g) of sub-section (1) of section`
  line `4 may be terminated before the expiry of the period of five years by the Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2006, s. 3, for section 5 (w.e.f. 21-12-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 39 of 2019, s. 3 (w.e.f. 5-12-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (17085)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Property vested in Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17085&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `All the property and funds set out in the Schedule to this Act and`
  line `all other property, whether movable or immovable which may hereafter be given, bequeathed or`
  line `otherwise transferred for the purposes of the Memorial or acquired for the said purposes shall vest in the`
  line Trustees.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (17086)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of Trustees to appoint committee of management.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17086&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of managing`
  line `the affairs of the Trust, the Trustees may, by resolution passed at a meeting, appoint a committee of`
  line `management, and entrust to it such powers, duties and functions, under such directions and limitations, as`
  line `may be defined by such resolution.`
  line
  line `(2) The Trustees may appoint any person as members of the committee of management, whether such`
  line `person are Trustees or not, and may, from time to time, vary or rescind any resolution passed by it under`
  line `this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (17087)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to approve audited accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 2006, s. 4 (w.e.f. 21-12-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17087&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Power to approve audited accounts.--The Trust shall meet at least once in a year to approve`
  line `the audited accounts of the Trust and shall transact such other business as may be considered necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (17088)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Validity of acts of Trustees not to be questioned by reason of vacancy, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17088&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No act of the`
  line `Trustees shall be deemed to be invalid merely by reason any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution`
  line `of, the body of Trustees.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (17089)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.(w.e.f. 21-12-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17089&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Accounts and audit.---(1) The accounts of the Trust shall be audited by the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in`
  line `connection with such audit shall be payable by the Trust to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(2) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Trust under this Act shall, have the same rights and privileges and the`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the`
  line `office of the Trust.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Trust as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or any other person`
  line `appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded annually to the`
  line `Central Government by the Trust and the Central Government shall cause the audit report to be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be, after it is received, before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (17090)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17090&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the objects of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which funds belonging to the Memorial shall be kept deposited or invested;`
  line
  line `(b) the mode of authentication of orders for payment of money by the Trustees;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which accounts shall be kept by the Trustees and the audit and publication of such`
  line accounts;
  line
  line `(d) the laying out, erection, improvement, maintenance and management of the Memorial and the`
  line `care and custody of the properties thereof.`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions under which the public shall have access to the Memorial or particular parts`
  line `thereof and the regulation of the conduct of persons entering the precincts of the Memorial;`
  line
  line `(f) the preservation of, and the prevention of injury to or interference with, any property vested in`
  line `the Trustees and the prevention of persons from trespassing into any particular part of the Memorial.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
  line
  line `(3) A rule made under this section made provide that a breach of any rule made under clauses (e) and`
  line `(f) of sub-section (2) shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (17091)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Trustees to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17091&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Trustees may make regulations consistent with`
  line `this Act for all or any of the following purposes, namely;--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which meetings of the Trustees shall be convened the quorum for the transaction`
  line `of any business thereat and the procedure at such meetings;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which a majority decision of the Trustees shall be obtained by circulation to the`
  line `Trustees of the matter requiring decision;`
  line
  line `(c) the term of office of members of the committee of management their powers and duties, and the`
  line `circumstances in which and the conditions subject to which such powers and duties may be exercised;`
  line
  line `(d) the appointment of such officers and servants as may be necessary for the purposes of the Trust,`
  line `and their terms and conditions of service.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (17092)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 13
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 2006, s. 6, for section 10 (w.e.f. 21-12-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154&sectionId=17092&sectionno=10A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00023_195125_1517807327154
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.--Every rule or regulation made under`
  line `this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in`
  line `session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.]`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
